    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 997-generation Carrera S is a definitive example of analog precision, preserved in concours-level condition. Powered by a rear-mounted 3.8L flat-six engine, the M97.01 powerplant delivers linear power through a 6-speed manual transaxle with a factory short-throw shifter. The chassis is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and a limited-slip differential, providing exceptional lateral grip and communicative steering feedback. The exterior retains its factory-applied finish with zero evidence of road rash or clear coat failure, while the interior maintains its original matte texture with no bolster wear or leather shrinkage. Recent preventative maintenance includes a comprehensive borescope inspection to confirm cylinder wall integrity and a full fluid flush. This is a mechanically transparent, high-performance specimen for the discerning collector.",
      "price": 48500.0,
